	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I wouldn't go to Famicomworld for any info... Besides, most of the amp circuits out there aren't designed properly for the job.
<br />
<br /><img src="http://img213.imageshack.us/img213/7609/circuit.jpg" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />You can use any general purpose PNP transistor. 
<br />
<br />You should definitely remove the RF modulator if it's still present so it doesn't affect the mod.
<br />
<br />For audio connect the positive leg of a 10uF capacitor to the cartridge connector pin 46, and the negative leg to your audio output. I'm not sure what the level is/if it also should be buffered but that's a better start.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
